This is very commonly used section by most of the companies. Here are important formulas & definitions for you.

Cost price: The price at which article is purchased is known as C.P.

Selling price: The price at which article is sold is known as S.P.

Profit or gain:  In mathematical terms we say if S.P is greater than C.P, then seller is said to have incurred profit or gain.

Loss: If Selling Price S.P is less than Cost price C.P, the seller is said to have incurred Loss.
